To derive the Tutte-Berge formula, we need to show that $\nu(G) = \min_{Z \subseteq V} \frac{1}{2}(|V| + |Z| - \text{odd}(G - Z))$. 

The key insight is that the expression $\frac{1}{2}(|V| + |Z| - \text{odd}(G - Z))$ is minimized when $Z$ is a maximal set such that $\nu(G - Z) = \nu(G) - |Z|$. This is because for such a set $Z$, we have $\nu(G) = \frac{1}{2}(|V| + |Z| - \text{odd}(G - Z))$, and for any other set $Y$, we have $\nu(G) \leq \frac{1}{2}(|V| + |Y| - \text{odd}(G - Y))$.

